eager to acquire it? Is this deal enough to allow Molson to challenge BUD? I m
guessing that TAP's market is more on US and Canada, so the synergy of
TAP+StarBev might be better, and it's finally becoming a decent yielder.<<

This is not my read of the transaction. Inbev acquired BUD in 2009 and incurred
significant leverage due to this deal, so they shed a bunch of non-core assets.
One of those assets was Starbev apparently, which was sold to a private equity
outfit for ~3B$. Now TAP buys the Starbev for ~15% more. Given the market
development and the sharp reduction in financing cost since 2009, and the
decent EBITDA multiple (~11), the acquisition cost looks on the cheap side.

My take is that the market valuation for companies in Europe are somewhat
depressed due to the European issues and TAP got a lower price than otherwise
possible.
